ians_Tower/Images/Background_1.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://www.cafenet.plus.com/The_Magicians_Tower/Images/Background_1.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=druidsad>Druidsad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 7:48:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Mages Worst at Solo</span><hr size=1> OK....how can anyone say a Mage is great at solo, when it seems they are the worst solo class, this is what I found.<br>
If your pet is in a fight, especially a tough one, and you get attacked by another NPC.....well a Mage does not have root, snare, fear or anythign to fend off this new NPC while your pet is still engaged in a fight. Since the Mage is weak he cannot melee the NPC. At least the Necro and even Wizard have speed effect spells to escape. <br>
This is not a troll post or a rant....I thought being a Mage would be great solo....but by lvl 17 I realized it is not true. Why do folks keep saying you are good at solo? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zacatac>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1435<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 7:51:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages Worst at Solo</span><hr size=1> Never said we were the best, just good at soloing.  Any class that can still solo dark blues at 61 has to be considered a good solo class don't you think? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Baron Zacatac Soulwanderer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nibbledeneck>nibbledeneck</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.smilies.nl/muziek/music487.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 7:53:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Try this</span><hr size=1> /pet hold<br>
/pet back off<br>
&lt;target new NPC&gt;<br>
/pet attack<br>
<br>
The first NPC stays on your pet and your pet attacks the second one.<br>
<br>
Works with more than 2 NPCs too.<br>
<br>
Enjoy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=salashpenumbra>Salash Penumbra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 365<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 7:54:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages Worst at Solo</span><hr size=1> Your complaint: Mages are no good at solo<br>
Your reason: Mages are no good at escape if they get in trouble<br>
<br>
Solution: Make sure you don't get in trouble<br>
Result: Mages are great at soloing (pre-60 anyway) <p>Salash Penumbra - Summoner of Armies!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nucci01>Nucci 01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 8:21:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages Worst at Solo</span><hr size=1> Or you could simply run to the other side of your pet, if the mob is on same faction he'll stop and hit the pet in hopes of helping the original mob.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=392829">Nucci</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vaereimmortalitis>Vaere Immortalitis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 8:31:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages Worst at Solo</span><hr size=1> Mages are ok for solo before 60, after 60 we need groups.  We can kill the odd dark blue at 61, but PoP mobs simply chew up pets too fast to be safe anymore. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ravian>Ravian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 8:54:45 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages Worst at Solo</span><hr size=1> Not a flame but I feel your terribly wrong.  Mages might not be the best soloers but they are darn good.  I have soloed my way up to lvl 50 in just under 10days online time.  I have seen posts of people plvling people to that lvl in not much better time.  I also screw around alot so its not like I was 100% grind.  <br>
<br>
I would say that any class who can solo a yellow or a red up until lvl 40 is a pretty good solo class.  Not to mention handle more than two mobs at once (if your good).  I can solo yard trash in maidens eye at lvl 50 I would like to see many classes do that.  Its not eficient but thats not the topic.<br>
<br>
I also feel were very good at soloing dark blues.  I was in LGuk last night with my guild fooling around getting a guildy a fbss.  Well we got it and the guild left.  I was there all alone.  I decided to take a stroll around the place.  I got jumped by multiple mobs numerous times.  I was able to handle everything with my 49 earth pet.  I would get an add have pet attack it then root it then I would step back out of melee range.  Worked great. <br>
<br>
I had three dark blues on him at once.  No problem to handle them I just DSed pet and healed him I would nuke the mob that he was attacking to kill them quicker.  I dont know to many classes that can handle 3 mobs at once in a duengeon, and only a few who can when they have the entire zone to work with.  So all in all I think mages are darn good soloers and a very fun class to play.  MAGE POWAH !!!! <p><img src=http://www.legionoffyre.net/disappearing%20flame.gif><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=425856><b>Ravian Varior</b></a><img src=http://www.legionoffyre.net/disappearing%20flame.gif><br><a href=http://www.legionoffyre.net><b>----{}Legion of Fyer{}---</b></a><br><b>---LVL 49 Erudite Mage---</b><br><a href=http://pub17.ezboard.com/bxegony >----------Xegony----------</a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skidogg>SkiDogg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 9:07:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages Worst at Solo</span><hr size=1> Grp in RCY (pod) got an add.. I nuked it once with FoT got agro ran out side the CY along the ice wall, had SoE.  Mob was not slowed / snared in any way.  I ran from on end to the other stoped, casted, ran again. lvl 56-57 lightcralwer took me just over 60mana. Got over a full AAbub.... but i guess i suck at soloing.  <p>Master Shaiten Netiahs<br>
LvL 62 Arch Mage </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fashionmagician>FashionMagician</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 9:08:54 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages Worst at Solo</span><hr size=1> Level 1 to level 52, almost completely solo.  What wasnt solo were lower level friend leaching experience while I did what I normally did while soloing.  Advice:  <br>
<br>
1) READ THESE BOARDS!  This is the best information you will ever encounter regarding playing a Magician.  The larger portion of my tecniques and skills came from this board.<br>
<br>
2) Plan carefully.  Know your hunting ground.  Know what to pull and how to pull it.  Know where the roaming mobs are and deal with them whenever possible.<br>
<br>
3) If you do get an add.. DONT PANIC!  Train back across your pet and stop so that the add has its back to your pet.  Either it will agro automatically, or else target add and /pet back off and /pet attack add.  Your pet will turn, attack the add's back, and if you haven't nuked the add, gain instant agro.  Then just step back out of harms way and determine whether to assist, heal, or gate.<br>
<br>
4) Make hotkeys for all your pet commands.  Yes, some people like the pet command box, some people swear by it.  But I find that in a tense battle, the smaller buttons get harder to hit, and you definitely dont want to hit that /pet get lost button by accident.<br>
<br>
I have played several other classes.  I play best at being a mage.  My friends say I make it look easy.  I just tell them I had very good instructors.  Thanks guys =)<br>
<br>
 <p><B>Zress</B> <BR>
<B>Fashion Magician</B> <BR> <I> <B>"((POOF!)) Your in style!"</I> </B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=calebe>Calebe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 567<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 9:11:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages Worst at Solo</span><hr size=1> As said we can solo all the way to 60, but once you hit 61 your soloing goes way down.<br>
<br>
It isn't can we kill a dark blue if everything goes right, your prepared, and full mana. Can you solo like in the past, and the answer is no.<br>
<br>
Pets are shredded to quickly, and mobs hit so hard 2 on a pet means gate or die. I would say run, but training the graveyard is not something I do, or like done having died to those trains a few times.<br>
<br>
The best escape is be lev'd, and head out over the highest peak you can find, a mob has to run up and down, and you gain some distance and gate out.<br>
<br>
Calebe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eandori>Eandori</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 415<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 9:23:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mages Worst at Solo</span><hr size=1> What a joke, worst at solo.<br>
<br>
Hey, I got a great idea.  How about I start an Enchanter and by level 17 I make a judgement on how the good the class is.  Because I'm obviously an expert by that time.<br>
<br>
Then I'll start a cleric, play him until I get my first newbie rez spell.  Then I'll send /tells to a 65 cleric and inform him how I think he should play his class.<br>
<br>
Sorry, but you deserved that.  Had you posted &quot;can somebody help me with soloing my mage&quot; I would help.  But you obviosly don't know much about this class and you post on our message board a very ignorant statement. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Baron Eandori Raintree<br>
61st Arch Mage of Solusek Ro <br>
 <br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36994">My Magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/enigmasolro">The Lords of Prophecy</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=heofmanyfals>HeOfManyFals</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 9:33:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Yeah,right</span><hr size=1> Worst at solo indeed.<br>
<br>
<br>
This is my fourth &quot;solo&quot; class and so far the mage is, in my opinion, the second best soloer in the game.<br>
<br>
<br>
As for adds, just run em over your pet, you goober. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=druidsad>Druidsad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 9:51:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  solo</span><hr size=1> I apologize for coming on strong. I should have wored it better. It's just I hear how great Mages are at solo, yet when an NPC add on comes at me...I run to pet, the mob still attacks me from behind and never aggro's on my pet. My pet sits there fighting my first mob and i die from the second. I am frustrated.<br>
I see Necro's cast darkness/fear on adds and then gate if necessary. I just didn't know how a Mage can survive.<br>
When I hit pet back off, the first mob keeps attacking it and my pet then engages in battle again, leaving me to fight the add on alone.<br>
BTW- At what level can you fight RED cons and what mobs are these? Don't you get resists from reds? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naladini>naladini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 589<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 9:53:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Yeah,right</span><hr size=1> I think what this poster fails to realise is that mages are not a 'cookie-cutter' class. <br>
<br>
There are certain spots in this game where we fair better than others, and they don't align well with someone who has done a lot of kiting/snaring/dotting.<br>
<br>
Its just a matter of actually learning how to play as a mage, and not a rooting class. <br>
<br>
This is a tough thing for some people to catch on to, especially when they're brining up alts. People expect to be able to take their new mage on exactly the same xp trip they went on with their previous characters, and that is usually not the most efficient way to go.<br>
<br>
This is why I suspect there aren't more mage alts popping up on all the servers, we're just too different.<br>
<br>
